#Step One:
-   Switch to root user on client computer
- Run apt install ssh -y
- Swich to .ssh directory
- Run ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "Proxmox"
- Run ssh-copy-id root@<Proxmox_IP_Address>
- Test ssh connection by running ssh root@<Proxmox_IP_Address>
- Run chown user:user id_rsa
- Run chmod 600 id_rsa
- Run cp id_rsa /home/user/.ssh/
- Switch back to normal user

#Step Two:
- Open VS Code
- Install "Remote - SSH" extension
- Press F1 and select "Remote-SSH: Open Configuration File"
- Select the config file to edit
- Add the following configuration:
```Host Proxmox
    HostName <Proxmox_IP_Address>
    User root
    IdentityFile /home/user/.ssh/id_rsa
``` IdentitiesOnly yes
- Save and close the config file